{
  "stem": "868.2",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "The doors closed again.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "We were told immediately to disembark, to get off the trucks and assemble in front of two tables with German soldiers sitting there.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "And an officer explained that we have to surrender everything, money, jewels, cuff links, everything.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "And one by one, we approached the table.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "They took down our names, [PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] the components of the family.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "And we were ordered into empty stables.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "I found out later that this used to be the headquarters of an Italian cavalry regiment, now abandoned, and taken over entirely by the Germans.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "There wasn't one Italian in, in, inside.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "So naturally, they had no use for horses.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "So they cleared the stables.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "And we were told to get in there and, and wait.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "As time passed during the day more and more Jews were being brought in.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "It turned out, again later-- something I didn't know at the time-- that this was a thoroughly methodically organized raid on all Jews of France-- of France-- of Florence.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "They knew where most of them were, were hidden, even in convents and other institutions.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 56,
      "text": "So I feared at any moment to see my mother walk, walk in.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 57,
      "text": "But it turned towards evening, and I didn't see my, my mother yet.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 58,
      "text": "In the evening, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] a German soldier came and said, I need some volunteers to bring in some more straw.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 59,
      "text": "So I went with a friend of mine, same age, called Sigi.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 60,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And we were brought by the German soldier to some kind of barn there where they had straw.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 61,
      "text": "We piled up the straw, as much as we could carry, and brought it back to the stables where we had been held.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
